One degree negative is OK ( i like more ).
A rudimentary check can be achieved with a two-foot level,
vehicle on level ground, place level against rim and measure the
amount from the rim out to the level, 1/4 " is about a degree of camber.
I doubt if you have the tools to check for a bent spindle.
